commentText: Tests that the REST handler URLs are properly sorted.
codeText: @Test_	public void testRestHandlerUrlSorting() {_		final int numberHandlers = 5___		final List<String> handlerUrls = new ArrayList<>(numberHandlers)___		handlerUrls.add("/jobs/overview")__		handlerUrls.add("/jobs/:jobid")__		handlerUrls.add("/jobs")__		handlerUrls.add("/:*")__		handlerUrls.add("/jobs/:jobid/config")___		final List<String> expected = new ArrayList<>(numberHandlers)___		expected.add("/jobs")__		expected.add("/jobs/overview")__		expected.add("/jobs/:jobid")__		expected.add("/jobs/:jobid/config")__		expected.add("/:*")___		Collections.sort(handlerUrls, new RestServerEndpoint.RestHandlerUrlComparator.CaseInsensitiveOrderComparator())___		assertEquals(expected, handlerUrls)__	}
